##########################
#run_multiple_species.sh #
##########################


Created By: Justin Miller
Email: jmiller@byu.edu

##########################

ARGUMENT OPTIONS:

 -h, --help    							show this help message and exit
 -i required input directory			Contains .fasta and .gff3 files. Must contain same base name (e.g., h_sapiens.gff3 and h_sapiens.fasta.gz)
 -o	required output directory			New Directory where JustOrthologs pairwise output files will be written.
 -e	required end output file			This will contain the ortholog groups after combining the pairwise comparisons
 -f optional extension for fasta files in the input directory. Default=.fasta"
 -g optional extension for gff3 files in the input directory. Default=.gff3"

##########################


Example usage:

bash run_multiple_species.sh -i smallTest/wrapperTest/ -o outputDir/ -e output_ortholog_groups -f .fasta.gz -g .gff3

Running the above command will produce a single output file called output_ortholog_groups in the current directory. 
It will also produce all pairwise comparisons for the species found in smallTest/wrapperTest.
For us, this command took approximately 4 minutes of user time.

